# Developer Agent Context Summary

## Last Run: 2026-03-14

## Completed Work This Session

### fieldmarshal: Full implementation, phases 2-6 (Tasks #433-437)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/fieldmarshal

Modern dataclass serialization library (dataclasses-json replacement). Zero dependencies, Python 3.10+.

- `@dataclass_json` decorator with `to_json()`, `from_json()`, `to_dict()`, `from_dict()`
- Nested dataclass support (recursive)
- Collection types: `list`, `dict`, `set`, `tuple`, `Optional`, `Union`
- `FieldConfig`: field rename, exclude, custom encoder/decoder, defaults
- `LetterCase`: camelCase, PascalCase, snake_case, kebab-case auto-conversion
- Built-in handlers: datetime, date, time, UUID, Decimal, Enum, Path, bytes
- Strict/lenient modes (unknown fields, type coercion)
- 57 tests, mypy strict, ruff clean
- README with full API docs + dataclasses-json migration guide
- CI green (Python 3.10-3.13, ubuntu+macos)
- Bumped CI to setup-python@v6, setup-uv@v7

**Note:** Python 3.14 treats `dataclasses.MISSING` as "no default" — used custom `_MISSING` sentinel in FieldConfig.

